00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:12.180 align:middle line:84%
at Canada's Wonderland,
you know, where I'm just,

00:01:12.180 --> 00:01:14.130 align:middle line:84%
like, holding on for
my life to the bar.

00:01:14.130 --> 00:01:19.576 align:middle line:84%
And it's been like up the hill,
you know, like, ah, ah, ah!

00:01:19.576 --> 00:01:20.580 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:20.580 --> 00:01:25.140 align:middle line:84%
It all started when I was on
a trip in Southern California.

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:27.540 align:middle line:84%
On the winter solstice,
I was driving up

00:01:27.540 --> 00:01:31.860 align:middle line:84%
to a Tibetan monastery,
Karma Mahasiddha Ling,

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:33.840 align:middle line:84%
high in the mountains
in Idyllwild,

00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:37.260 align:middle line:84%
which is in the high
desert above Palm Springs.

00:01:37.260 --> 00:01:40.350 align:middle line:84%
And I had the windows rolled
down in my Jeep Cherokee.

00:01:40.350 --> 00:01:43.590 align:middle line:84%
And I'm singing, and
chanting, and praying.

00:01:43.590 --> 00:01:46.500 align:middle line:84%
My religious practice
is Tibetan Buddhist,

00:01:46.500 --> 00:01:49.990 align:middle line:84%
so I was doing this Tibetan
chant to Holy Mother Tara, Om

00:01:49.990 --> 00:01:52.740 align:middle line:90%
Tare Tuttare Ture Svaha.

00:01:52.740 --> 00:01:54.180 align:middle line:90%
I had a very happy mind.

00:01:54.180 --> 00:01:56.550 align:middle line:84%
I was going up to
morning prayers.

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:58.950 align:middle line:84%
And this is this
very remote road

00:01:58.950 --> 00:02:03.270 align:middle line:84%
that winds up about 14,000
feet from the desert floor.

00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:04.830 align:middle line:90%
And there's no guardrail.

00:02:04.830 --> 00:02:08.340 align:middle line:84%
And the road is along the
outside of the mountain.

00:02:08.340 --> 00:02:11.810 align:middle line:84%
And the monastery is right
at the top of the mountain.

00:02:11.810 --> 00:02:15.780 align:middle line:84%
And as I'm driving up-- it's,
like, 9 AM in the morning--

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:18.970 align:middle line:84%
there's this woman standing
at the side of the road.

00:02:18.970 --> 00:02:20.910 align:middle line:90%
And I thought she looked cold.

00:02:20.910 --> 00:02:24.690 align:middle line:84%
She had a cloth coat on,
a very thin cloth coat.

00:02:24.690 --> 00:02:27.210 align:middle line:84%
And I knew if I
stopped to pick her up,

00:02:27.210 --> 00:02:29.790 align:middle line:84%
I'd miss the morning
prayers, but something in me

00:02:29.790 --> 00:02:31.560 align:middle line:90%
told me to pick her up.

00:02:31.560 --> 00:02:32.400 align:middle line:90%
So I picked her up.

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:35.820 align:middle line:84%
And apparently, she was a
house keeper in the desert.

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:38.550 align:middle line:84%
She had missed her last
bus up the mountain.

00:02:38.550 --> 00:02:41.470 align:middle line:84%
And her children had
stayed alone for the night.

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:43.830 align:middle line:84%
And I felt very
troubled for her,

00:02:43.830 --> 00:02:46.890 align:middle line:84%
so I made a point of bringing
her directly to her home.

00:02:46.890 --> 00:02:49.470 align:middle line:84%
And while we were
driving, she said to me,

00:02:49.470 --> 00:02:51.780 align:middle line:90%
don't drive off the cliff today.

00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:55.140 align:middle line:84%
And I grew up in snow
storms in Northern Ontario.

00:02:55.140 --> 00:02:57.990 align:middle line:84%
I got my driver's
license in a snow storm.

00:02:57.990 --> 00:03:00.660 align:middle line:84%
And I've driven in icy
conditions, in whiteouts,

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:04.060 align:middle line:90%
you know, for over 25 years.

00:03:04.060 --> 00:03:07.240 align:middle line:84%
And so I said, you know,
no, don't worry about me.

00:03:07.240 --> 00:03:08.040 align:middle line:90%
I'll be fine.

00:03:08.040 --> 00:03:10.170 align:middle line:84%
You know, like, and
this is the desert.

00:03:10.170 --> 00:03:12.270 align:middle line:84%
You know, what can
possibly happen?

00:03:12.270 --> 00:03:14.850 align:middle line:84%
So I brought her to her
house and dropped her off.

00:03:14.850 --> 00:03:16.900 align:middle line:90%
And she peered in the window.

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.800 align:middle line:84%
And again she said, don't
drive off the cliff today.

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.150 align:middle line:84%
And she looked me
directly in the eyes.

00:03:22.150 --> 00:03:23.910 align:middle line:90%
And I said no, no, no, I'm fine.

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:26.500 align:middle line:90%
You know, don't worry about it.

00:03:26.500 --> 00:03:28.050 align:middle line:90%
So I'm driving up.

00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:29.640 align:middle line:90%
I went around another corner.

00:03:29.640 --> 00:03:32.190 align:middle line:84%
And it started to snow,
because, of course,

00:03:32.190 --> 00:03:35.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm moving up through the
elevation very quickly.

00:03:35.200 --> 00:03:36.780 align:middle line:84%
And I had my shorts
and a top on.

00:03:36.780 --> 00:03:39.030 align:middle line:90%
It gets colder and colder.

00:03:39.030 --> 00:03:40.380 align:middle line:90%
I rolled up my windows.

00:03:40.380 --> 00:03:43.200 align:middle line:84%
The snow started hitting
the windshield furiously.

00:03:43.200 --> 00:03:44.670 align:middle line:90%
It turned to hail.

00:03:44.670 --> 00:03:46.230 align:middle line:90%
I went into four-wheel drive.

00:03:46.230 --> 00:03:47.715 align:middle line:90%
I'm being very careful.

00:03:47.715 --> 00:03:51.960 align:middle line:84%
I round a corner and the Jeep
goes out of control right out

00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:55.950 align:middle line:84%
from under me and starts rolling
over the side of the cliff.

00:03:55.950 --> 00:03:58.920 align:middle line:84%
And I just thought,
I'm going to die today.

00:03:58.920 --> 00:04:01.440 align:middle line:84%
You know, like, I'm on my
way to Tibetan prayers.

00:04:01.440 --> 00:04:04.110 align:middle line:90%
And I'm going to die today.

00:04:04.110 --> 00:04:07.860 align:middle line:84%
The only thing I could think
of doing from my meditation

00:04:07.860 --> 00:04:10.920 align:middle line:90%
practice was to call out--

00:04:10.920 --> 00:04:13.260 align:middle line:84%
in Tibetan prayers, you
call it refuge, call

00:04:13.260 --> 00:04:17.670 align:middle line:84%
to the holy mother, Om Tare
Tuttare Ture Svaha, which,

00:04:17.670 --> 00:04:20.700 align:middle line:84%
the translation from Sanskrit
is, Holy Mother, please

00:04:20.700 --> 00:04:23.285 align:middle line:90%
come to my aid.

00:04:23.285 --> 00:04:26.790 align:middle line:84%
As I called that out, the
thought occurred to me,

00:04:26.790 --> 00:04:28.920 align:middle line:84%
oh my god, they're going
to telephone my mother

00:04:28.920 --> 00:04:31.110 align:middle line:84%
and tell her that
I've died today.

00:04:31.110 --> 00:04:34.500 align:middle line:84%
And I just felt so much
grief in my heart and pain

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:37.290 align:middle line:84%
for my mother to get this
phone call, thinking,

00:04:37.290 --> 00:04:39.000 align:middle line:90%
this would kill her.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:41.340 align:middle line:84%
And I just called out
to the Holy Mother

00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:45.600 align:middle line:84%
again in Sanskrit, Om
Tare Tuttare Ture Svaha.

00:04:45.600 --> 00:04:48.270 align:middle line:84%
And my Jeep stopped
halfway down the mountain,

00:04:48.270 --> 00:04:51.100 align:middle line:90%
upside down on a stone.

00:04:51.100 --> 00:04:53.550 align:middle line:84%
A large boulder had
stopped the Jeep.

00:04:53.550 --> 00:04:55.560 align:middle line:90%
And I was pinned in it.

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:57.750 align:middle line:84%
The hood of the car
was ripped totally off.

00:04:57.750 --> 00:04:59.820 align:middle line:90%
The ceiling was caved in.

00:04:59.820 --> 00:05:02.880 align:middle line:84%
I couldn't undo the seat
belt. It was still in drive,

00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:05.320 align:middle line:84%
but the car was
completely turned off.

00:05:05.320 --> 00:05:07.767 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't know
if I was paralyzed.

00:05:07.767 --> 00:05:09.100 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know what had happened.

00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.980 align:middle line:90%
So I pinched myself.

00:05:10.980 --> 00:05:12.760 align:middle line:90%
And I could feel everything.

00:05:12.760 --> 00:05:14.220 align:middle line:90%
I felt OK.

00:05:14.220 --> 00:05:16.230 align:middle line:90%
And I was just so thankful.

00:05:16.230 --> 00:05:19.980 align:middle line:84%
So I managed to push myself up
somehow against the ceiling,

00:05:19.980 --> 00:05:22.740 align:middle line:84%
and undo the seat belt,
and drop upside down.

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:26.640 align:middle line:84%
And the hood of the car was
in a very precarious position.

00:05:26.640 --> 00:05:30.510 align:middle line:84%
So I managed to crawl
out of the broken glass

00:05:30.510 --> 00:05:32.400 align:middle line:84%
and start crawling
up the mountain.

00:05:32.400 --> 00:05:36.360 align:middle line:84%
And there was some kind of
forest fire station up there.

00:05:36.360 --> 00:05:39.090 align:middle line:84%
And this man had seen
me go over the cliff

00:05:39.090 --> 00:05:40.110 align:middle line:90%
in his rear-view mirror.

00:05:40.110 --> 00:05:42.540 align:middle line:84%
And he had a CB radio
or a cell phone,

00:05:42.540 --> 00:05:43.800 align:middle line:90%
and called for an ambulance.

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:45.990 align:middle line:90%
And I was totally in shock.

00:05:45.990 --> 00:05:49.620 align:middle line:90%
So move fast forward to--

00:05:49.620 --> 00:05:51.390 align:middle line:84%
I was, you know,
went to the hospital.

00:05:51.390 --> 00:05:53.820 align:middle line:84%
I broke several ribs
and fractured them,

00:05:53.820 --> 00:05:57.810 align:middle line:84%
injured my neck, my low back,
had glass shards in my arms,

00:05:57.810 --> 00:06:00.060 align:middle line:90%
my face, my legs.

00:06:00.060 --> 00:06:02.710 align:middle line:84%
I returned back to
Toronto, Canada.

00:06:02.710 --> 00:06:06.300 align:middle line:84%
And I was in terrible pain
and had a very difficult time

00:06:06.300 --> 00:06:08.340 align:middle line:90%
healing from the broken ribs.

00:06:08.340 --> 00:06:13.140 align:middle line:84%
And the whole year of 1998,
I was in terrible suffering.

00:06:13.140 --> 00:06:15.510 align:middle line:84%
I went to the Roman
Catholic Church.

00:06:15.510 --> 00:06:18.160 align:middle line:84%
And I lit a candle
to the Virgin Mary.

00:06:18.160 --> 00:06:20.500 align:middle line:84%
And I prayed for some
kind of guidance.

00:06:20.500 --> 00:06:21.610 align:middle line:90%
Like, what is this about?

00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:24.550 align:middle line:90%
Is my life as it was over?

00:06:24.550 --> 00:06:28.210 align:middle line:84%
I had been very active as a
documentary filmmaker doing

00:06:28.210 --> 00:06:30.130 align:middle line:90%
social justice issues.

00:06:30.130 --> 00:06:32.260 align:middle line:84%
And I was not able
to be a vital part

00:06:32.260 --> 00:06:36.910 align:middle line:84%
of the community due to constant
physical and emotional pain.

00:06:36.910 --> 00:06:39.400 align:middle line:84%
And I was feeling more and
more depressed and frustrated,

00:06:39.400 --> 00:06:40.810 align:middle line:90%
like my life was over.

00:06:40.810 --> 00:06:43.900 align:middle line:84%
My religion that I was born
into was Roman Catholic.

00:06:43.900 --> 00:06:45.820 align:middle line:84%
And my religion of
choice as an adult

00:06:45.820 --> 00:06:47.800 align:middle line:90%
has been Tibetan Buddhism.

00:06:47.800 --> 00:06:50.440 align:middle line:84%
So I lit a candle
to the Virgin Mary.

00:06:50.440 --> 00:06:53.620 align:middle line:84%
And I prayed very sincerely, you
know, what is this all about?

00:06:53.620 --> 00:06:54.850 align:middle line:90%
Please show me.

00:06:54.850 --> 00:06:57.160 align:middle line:90%
And I had a dream that night.

00:06:57.160 --> 00:07:01.030 align:middle line:84%
And in the dream, I saw
myself directing and producing

00:07:01.030 --> 00:07:06.760 align:middle line:84%
a live show of Rumi's poetry,
Mevlana Jelaluddin Rumi

00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:09.940 align:middle line:84%
is a Sufi poet from
the 13th Century.

00:07:09.940 --> 00:07:12.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was a little bit
familiar with his poetry.

00:07:12.700 --> 00:07:15.130 align:middle line:84%
I had a few of his
books, but he was not

00:07:15.130 --> 00:07:18.110 align:middle line:90%
a moving force in my life.

00:07:18.110 --> 00:07:20.650 align:middle line:84%
So this dream kept
on nagging at me.

00:07:20.650 --> 00:07:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And I wondered what
it was really about.

00:07:22.420 --> 00:07:25.970 align:middle line:84%
There were no other messages
that came to me at that time.

00:07:25.970 --> 00:07:26.950 align:middle line:90%
So I followed up.

00:07:26.950 --> 00:07:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And I called Coleman Barks, who
is one of the world's leading

00:07:30.370 --> 00:07:32.410 align:middle line:90%
translators of Rumi.

00:07:32.410 --> 00:07:35.860 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you know, I'm this
crazy independent filmmaker

00:07:35.860 --> 00:07:37.000 align:middle line:90%
from Toronto, Canada.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:39.870 align:middle line:84%
I tried to talk him
out of helping me out.

00:07:39.870 --> 00:07:42.040 align:middle line:84%
Or you know, I wanted
him to say, don't worry,

00:07:42.040 --> 00:07:45.460 align:middle line:84%
people have dreams like this all
the time, don't worry about it.

00:07:45.460 --> 00:07:47.950 align:middle line:84%
And he listened
to my whole story.

00:07:47.950 --> 00:07:50.680 align:middle line:84%
And then he said
to me, everybody's

00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:52.960 align:middle line:90%
got to follow their dream.

00:07:52.960 --> 00:07:54.640 align:middle line:84%
And I started
crying on the phone.

00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:57.880 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that I was being
called to do something.

00:07:57.880 --> 00:08:01.600 align:middle line:84%
And I wasn't quite sure where
it was going to take me.

00:08:01.600 --> 00:08:07.280 align:middle line:84%
So fast forward to
October 23, 1999,

00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:09.700 align:middle line:84%
which was my 44th
birthday, my birthday

00:08:09.700 --> 00:08:13.640 align:middle line:84%
present that year was to produce
and direct a live show of Rumi.

00:08:13.640 --> 00:08:15.440 align:middle line:90%
It was very successful.

00:08:15.440 --> 00:08:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I think we had 500 people on the
Friday night and the Saturday

00:08:18.200 --> 00:08:19.000 align:middle line:90%
night.

00:08:19.000 --> 00:08:22.420 align:middle line:84%
And people were just
raised to ecstatic heights

00:08:22.420 --> 00:08:27.280 align:middle line:84%
by the poetry of this
beautiful philosopher, Rumi.

00:08:27.280 --> 00:08:30.040 align:middle line:84%
After that, I showed
some of the footage

00:08:30.040 --> 00:08:33.010 align:middle line:84%
to a producer at
VisionTV in Canada.

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:35.860 align:middle line:84%
And I received encouragement
from several people

00:08:35.860 --> 00:08:39.340 align:middle line:84%
to pursue a documentary
film about the work

00:08:39.340 --> 00:08:42.980 align:middle line:84%
and the philosophy of Rumi
at work in the world today.

00:08:42.980 --> 00:08:46.240 align:middle line:84%
And I noticed that,
during this process,

00:08:46.240 --> 00:08:48.510 align:middle line:84%
the medical doctors couldn't
do anything with me.

00:08:48.510 --> 00:08:50.270 align:middle line:90%
Painkillers didn't work.

00:08:50.270 --> 00:08:51.580 align:middle line:90%
I was in constant pain.

00:08:51.580 --> 00:08:55.270 align:middle line:84%
I had terrible anxiety
and mental stress.

00:08:55.270 --> 00:08:58.870 align:middle line:84%
And somewhere during this
process of producing the show,

00:08:58.870 --> 00:09:01.210 align:middle line:84%
the pain had
completely dropped off.

00:09:01.210 --> 00:09:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And I became happier,
and happier, and happier.

00:09:05.080 --> 00:09:06.940 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden,
I found myself

00:09:06.940 --> 00:09:09.040 align:middle line:84%
giving birth to this
amazing project that

00:09:09.040 --> 00:09:10.840 align:middle line:84%
was about the healing
of the planet.

00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:15.790 align:middle line:84%
My whole life was changed by
this driving off the cliff.

00:09:15.790 --> 00:09:18.310 align:middle line:84%
And having this
experience opened up

00:09:18.310 --> 00:09:21.180 align:middle line:90%
a whole new world for me.

00:09:21.180 --> 00:09:23.770 align:middle line:84%
And it's brought incredible
riches into my life

00:09:23.770 --> 00:09:28.960 align:middle line:84%
that I couldn't possibly ever
have dreamed of or imagined.

00:09:28.960 --> 00:09:34.120 align:middle line:84%
My whole vision as a film maker
from this very narrow focus

00:09:34.120 --> 00:09:37.810 align:middle line:84%
has moved into a more
global focus, Rumi, being

00:09:37.810 --> 00:09:40.630 align:middle line:84%
a Sufi mystic, who,
in his lifetime,

00:09:40.630 --> 00:09:44.770 align:middle line:84%
promoted world peace, tolerance
for different religions.

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:47.900 align:middle line:84%
A quote from Rumi, "I am neither
Muslim, Christian, Buddhist,

00:09:47.900 --> 00:09:48.700 align:middle line:90%
or a Jew.

00:09:48.700 --> 00:09:50.530 align:middle line:90%
I belong to the beloved."

00:09:50.530 --> 00:09:53.080 align:middle line:84%
Working with the Rumi
material certainly

00:09:53.080 --> 00:09:55.850 align:middle line:84%
has expanded my
vision of the world

00:09:55.850 --> 00:09:59.290 align:middle line:84%
and given me fire
and passion to really

